			<div class="comment_body">
				<div class="comment_time">
					04:20 PM on 09/02/2013				</div>

																												
				The ACA does more damage than that even. The ACA plus S.744 gives employers here in the U.S. a serious incentive to hire foreign workers instead of Americans. <a href="http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2013/aug/27/mccain-immigration-bill-could-give-foreign-workers/?utm_source=feedly" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2013/aug/27/mccain-immigration-bill-could-give-foreign-workers/?utm_source=feedly</a><br />
"Two Republicans who helped write the Senates immigration bill said Tuesday that they are convinced it will finally be able to get a handle on the porous southwestern border  but acknowledged it could mean problems for American workers.<br />
Sens. John McCain and Jeff Flake, both Arizona Republicans, said they fear that foreign workers will be more attractive to hire than Americans for some companies because the foreigners wont be eligible for the same health care benefits."<br />
<br />
For high-wage workers it might be less of an incentive to hire foreign nationals but for low-wage workers it will be a big difference. The mandate has been delayed until 2015 but employers hiring for beyond the short term know that the mandate is coming and that it benefits them directly to hire foreign nationals over Americans.			</div>
			
