That's because Obama proposed a whopping $2 increase - not even enough to lift an earner out from under the poverty level. <br />
<br />
The working class is on the ropes and there is no help in sight. The Dems current pitiful performance on domestic and foreign affairs means they won't pick up many seats in the house for 2014 and the Dems will do their best to nominate a former Walmart board board member for president in 2016. <br />
<br />
Working people need to stick together, support each others strikes and keep reminding ourselves of the words of Abraham Lincoln:<br />
<br />
"Labor is prior to, and independent of, capital. Capital is only the fruit of labor, and could never have existed if labor had not first existed. Labor is the superior of capital, and deserves much the higher consideration."			</div>
			
