		<div id="comment_280964658" class="comment_item published_comment " style="margin-left: 0px; display:block" >
						<div class="comment_top">
				
				<div class="comment_top_inner clearfix">

					
		  <div id="comment_icons_280964658" class="float_right">
											
													
							<div class="badge_sprite badge_networker1" userid="1497352" userlevel="networker1">
							</div>
																				</div> <!-- end of comment_icons -->
					
					<div class="author_name ">
												<a class="arial_14 bold vertical_color" href="/social/S_M_V?action=comments">S M V</a>

						<div class="bio_teaser clearfix">
							Give me your tired, your poor, Your huddled masses						</div>

						<div class="author_fans">
							<a class="author_fans_count float_left padding_top_2" href="/social/S_M_V">120 Fans</a>
							
							                            						</div>
					</div>

									</div>
			</div>
			<div class="comment_body">
				<div class="comment_time">
					10:39 AM on 08/30/2013				</div>

																												
				"People who work full-time in America should not have to live in poverty -- simple as that. Too many jobs don't pay enough to get by, let alone get ahead."<br />
<br />
<br />
This statement is simply wrong. Pay is not and should not be determined based on the hours you work or the effort involved. Income is and needs to be determined by the value you create for others. In reality you create value and trade it to your employer or customer. They have to value what you contribute more than the money they pay you.<br />
<br />
A simple example: Imagine you believe you are a talented artist and you spend hundreds of hours painting what you think are brilliant pieces of art. How is the value of that art ultimately determined? ANSWER: You offer your paintings for sale and see what others are willing to pay for them. Notice the price you can sell your art for has nothing to do with the hours it took you to create, but on how much other value what you created. <br />
<br />
That ultimately is how wages and income is determined and unless people develop the skills and abilities to create more value higher wages are unsustainable. Until people accept this reality they will continue to pursue divisive policies that damage rather than enhance the wealth creating ability of the US economy.			</div>
			
